  <!-- SEOUL VISA ENTRY -->
  <section id="visa" class="home-section">
    <div class="home-container">
      <h2 class="home-section-title scroll-animate">Seoul Visa Entry</h2>
      <p class="home-section-intro scroll-animate" data-delay="0.1">Please review the visa and K-ETA requirements below based on your passport place of issue.</p>

      <div class="home-visa-list">
        <div class="home-visa-header" aria-hidden="true">
          <div>Visa Type</div>
          <div>Passport – Place of Issued</div>
          <div>Remark</div>
        </div>

        <article class="home-visa-card scroll-animate" data-delay="0.1">
          <div class="home-visa-cell home-visa-cell--type">
            <span class="home-visa-label">Visa Type</span>
            <span class="home-visa-type">Visa Exemption <span class="home-visa-sub">(K-ETA only)</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="home-visa-cell">
            <span class="home-visa-label">Passport – Place of Issued</span>
            <p>Australia, Fiji, Germany, Hong Kong SAR, Japan, Malaysia, New Zealand, Singapore, Taiwan, Thailand, and United Kingdom</p>
          </div>
          <div class="home-visa-cell home-visa-cell--remark">
            <span class="home-visa-label">Remark</span>
            <div class="home-visa-remark">
              <p>The K-ETA exemption is currently in effect until <strong>December 31, 2026</strong>. Individuals eligible for the exemption will receive a pop-up notification upon selecting their nationality during the application process.</p>
              <p>Recommendation: All nationals from visa waiver countries should apply for K-ETA first. If an exemption notification is received, they will be directed to apply for the E-Arrival Card (which is free of charge).</p>
              <p>For further information, consult the relevant Embassy of the Republic of Korea.</p>
              <p>Visa waiver countries need to apply for an online K-ETA or E-Arrival Card within 3 days before arrival in Korea. Paper arrival cards in South Korea have been officially discontinued.</p>
              <p><strong>K-ETA application:</strong> <a href="https://www.k-eta.go.kr/portal/newapply/index.do" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="home-link">www.k-eta.go.kr</a></p>
              <p><strong>E-Arrival card application:</strong> <a href="https://www.e-arrivalcard.go.kr/portal/main/index.do" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="home-link">www.e-arrivalcard.go.kr</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="home-visa-card scroll-animate" data-delay="0.2">
          <div class="home-visa-cell home-visa-cell--type">
            <span class="home-visa-label">Visa Type</span>
            <span class="home-visa-type">Visa (C-3)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="home-visa-cell">
            <span class="home-visa-label">Passport – Place of Issued</span>
            <p>Bangladesh, Cambodia, China, India, Indonesia, Laos, Myanmar, Nepal, Papua New Guinea, Philippines, Sri Lanka, and Vietnam</p>
          </div>
          <div class="home-visa-cell home-visa-cell--remark">
            <span class="home-visa-label">Remark</span>
            <div class="home-visa-remark">
              <p><strong>Important Note:</strong> Visa applications can take more than 14 working days to process. Please complete your visa application ahead of time before your departure.</p>
              <p><strong>Contact:</strong> Please contact EOY Country HR Champion for Visa Applications.</p>
              <p><strong>Key Requirements &amp; Process:</strong></p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Visa Type:</strong> For tourism or casual visits, you will apply for a Short-Term General Tourist Visa (C-3-9).</li>
                <li><strong>Application Process:</strong> Fill out an electronic visa form online via the Korea Visa Portal, print the generated e-form with a barcode, and take it along with your physical documents to the Embassy.</li>
                <li><strong>Embassy Fees:</strong> USD $40 for a single-entry visa.</li>
                <li><strong>Validity:</strong> Single-entry visas are typically valid for up to 90 days from the date of issuance.</li>
              </ul>
              <p><strong>Essential Documents:</strong></p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Passport:</strong> Original passport valid for at least 6 months beyond your departure date, with at least two blank pages.</li>
                <li><strong>Photograph:</strong> Recent passport-sized (35 × 45 mm) photos with a white background.</li>
                <li><strong>Financial Proof:</strong> Original bank statement for the last 3 months.</li>
                <li><strong>Proof of Employment / Business:</strong> A leave approval letter on an official company letterhead.</li>
                <li><strong>Travel Logistics:</strong> Confirmed round-trip flight ticket and hotel/accommodation reservation.</li>
              </ul>
              <p><strong>Additional Remarks:</strong></p>
              <ol>
                <li>For further details or to check the visa application status, refer to the <a href="https://www.visa.go.kr/openPage.do?MENU_ID=10101" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="home-link">Korea Visa Portal</a>.</li>
                <li>Remind to complete and submit the e-arrival card at <a href="https://www.e-arrivalcard.go.kr/portal/main/index.do" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="home-link">www.e-arrivalcard.go.kr</a> within 3 days before arrival in Korea.</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

